                <textarea name="" id="" class="p-3 form-control fs-14 fw-300" rows="8" style="resize: none;">In Turkey, the standard rule for issuing work permits (WP) to foreign employees requires a ratio of five local employees for every foreign employee (1:5 ratio). However, under certain circumstances, such as providing a strong reference letter, there may be flexibility in meeting this requirement. This exception allows companies to potentially bypass the ratio, making it easier to hire foreign talent while still aligning with Turkish labor regulations.</textarea>
